  "blurb": "Three beachfront villas stepping down landscaped terraces to a secluded stretch of Chaweng sand, gazing out to the uninhabited island of Koh Matlang. Take one villa or the whole estate — 21 bedrooms, four infinity pools, beachfront jacuzzis and an outdoor cinema. Samui's most-loved address for weddings and big-family gatherings.",
  "detail": "Three architect-designed villas sit side by side on a private, north-Chaweng beachfront, built across wide landscaped terraces that step down through lotus ponds and tropical gardens to a quiet stretch of sand. Booked together they sleep up to 72 across 21 bedrooms and four children's dorms; taken one at a time, each is a self-contained resort of six to eight suites. Every bedroom is ensuite — most with sea views and indoor-outdoor showers — and the master suites open straight to the water.\n\nThe grounds are built for big gatherings: four infinity pools, three oversized beachfront jacuzzis, open-plan lounges that fold open to the breeze, private cinema rooms, an estate gym, and a beach-garden spa of eight sea-view treatment salas. Steps from each villa lead directly onto the soft Samui sand, where kayaks and paddleboards wait, and an outdoor cinema turns the lawn into a screening room after dark.\n\nThe estate comes fully staffed — villa managers, private chefs, housekeepers, gardeners, pool attendants and night security — with daily breakfast, a welcome meal and airport transfers included. Long Samui's favourite address for weddings and multi-generational holidays, it offers the rare luxury of a secluded beach with Chaweng's restaurants and nightlife ten minutes away.",
